				<h2><a name="KeepIMHistory"></a>Do you keep history of your IM conversations?</h2>
                    <p>IM conversations often can be as if not more important than emails, because they are usually only 
					used for high priority issues or issues that need to be resolved now. Therefore it is very 
					important to keep history of all your IM conversations. They can often be used as a reference 
					point, or as a digital log of all the important issues that have been discussed. In fact, you 
					can be guaranteed that you will want to revisit something you have discussed before with 
					other employees.</p>		
			        <p>The only exception to this rule of course is when you're using a public computer, in which case privacy and security issues arise by keeping IM history on that computer.</p>
            </li>
            
            <li>
				<h2><a name="Research"></a>Do you investigate your question for two minutes before asking someone on IM?</h2>
			        <p>Always do a quick investigation before asking for help. When asking a question using IM, always start your conversation with "I have googled this and no luck".</p>
					<p>IM can interrupt a person when they are busy, so make sure that you are well prepared and have tried to find the solution another way first.</p>		
            </li>
            
